race.comment: EMERALD COURT (4) returns off a sizzling trial win and looks ready to fire fresh. She tackles a favoured trip and has no draw. Every chance to snap the drought. SHUTTLE RUN (5) hasn't been threatening but showed signs of life last start at Gawler. Drops back to a winning trip and gets Murtagh on, which could be the spark. SHIKANIC (2) failed in town but this is more his scene. He's fit, finds his pet distance, and can bounce back sharply. CRIMOSA (7) resumes for the Lynch yard and while he hasn't trialled, he's in a race that suits. Keep safe. CATALINA BLUE (10) is hit-and-miss but has won here before. Include in wider exotics.
